{% extends "jinja2/_base.html.jinja2" %}

{% block content %}
    <div id="home-section">
        <div class="intro">
            <div class="intro-text"></div><img src="assets/widener1.jpg">
        </div>

        <div class="main">
            <div class="blurb">
                <h2>Get recognized for your outstanding
                journalism.</h2>
            </div>

            <div class="home-testimonials">
                <h2>About the Awards</h2>

                <p>The objective of The Harvard
                Crimson&rsquo;s Journalism
                Awards program is to recognize superb
                journalism produced at the high school
                level. We will be taking entries from
                nearly all aspects of journalism, with
                categories including general news,
                features, sports and arts, opinion, and
                overall reporter, along with multimedia
                such as photo, video, and newspaper design.
                Given the rise of digital journalism,
                online publications are also encouraged to
                enter via a dedicated award category. All
                entries are eligible to receive comments
                and critique, as well as access to grading
                based on our proprietary
                internally-developed rubric.</p>

                <p>Please sign up under the
                &ldquo;Subscribe &amp;
                Contact&rdquo; page to receive more
                information as the entry period and
                deadlines are finalized. We look forward to
                reviewing your entry.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="home-crimson">
                <h2>About The Crimson</h2>

                <p>The Harvard Crimson, the nation's oldest
                continuously published daily college
                newspaper, was founded in 1873 and
                incorporated in 1967. The Crimson has a
                rich tradition of journalistic integrity
                and counts among its ranks of editorship
                some of America's greatest journalists. The
                faces of Pulitzer Prize-winning Crimson
                editors line the walls of The Crimson.</p>

                <p>The Crimson is proud of its legacy of
                alumni active in journalism, business,
                public service, and politics. Past editors
                include Franklin D. Roosevelt, Class of
                1904, John F. Kennedy '40, J. Anthony Lewis
                '48, Don Graham '65, Linda Greenhouse '68,
                Steve Ballmer '77, Jim Cramer '77, Susan
                Chira '80, and Jeff Zucker '86. Having
                grown from a fortnightly newspaper to a
                daily, 140 years after its founding The
                Crimson continues to flourish.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
{% endblock content %}
